<subSubSection pageId="168" pageNumber="169" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="168.[151,1436,438,861]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[267,515,690,717]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="243 - 274" refId="ref370928" refString="Rondani, C. (1875 a) Species italicae ordinis dipterorum (Muscaria Rndn.) collectae et observatae. Stirps XXII Lonchaeinae Rndn. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 6 (4) [1874], 243 - 274." type="journal article" year="1875">Rondani (1875a: 253)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1875" box="[638,837,690,717]" class="Insecta" family="Opomyzidae" genus="Geomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bracata">
<emphasis box="[638,837,690,717]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Geomyza bracata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from just the male sex, without specifying either the 
<taxonomicName box="[199,285,726,752]" family="Number" pageId="168" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
or the length of the specimens: “ 
<emphasis box="[658,861,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">lectus mas tantum</emphasis>
[collected the male only]”. Árpad Soós labeled the single MZUF male as “ 
<typeStatus box="[467,570,762,788]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">holotype</typeStatus>
” but he never indicated this specimen as 
<typeStatus box="[1049,1147,762,788]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">holotype</typeStatus>
in any of his publication (E.P. Nartshuk &amp; J.W.A. van Zuijlen, pers. comm., 2012). We consider it as a 
<typeStatus box="[1067,1154,799,825]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">syntype</typeStatus>
because Rondani did not specify he had a single specimen.
</paragraph>
